ProtoDefines:
. "If $f:(A,\rho)\to (A,\rho)$ is defined on all of $A$ and 
   there is a constant $\alpha$ in $(0,1)$ such that 
   \begin{equation} \rho(f(u),f(v))\le\alpha\rho(u,v) \quad for
   all\quad (u,v)\in A\times A, \end{equation} then $f$ is a 
   \term{ contraction } of $(A,\rho)$."
